undifferentiated heavy lifting.

258
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:06,570
And so we've already figured
out how to scale KMS,

259
00:12:06,570 --> 00:12:07,743
how to keep it healthy.

260
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:11,580
It is our highest level of SLA.

261
00:12:11,580 --> 00:12:15,450
We deliver KMS at a SLA of five nines.

262
00:12:15,450 --> 00:12:17,220
And in fact the reality is significantly

263
00:12:17,220 --> 00:12:18,470
more available than that.

264
00:12:20,070 --> 00:12:23,760
There's already transparent
rotation built into KMS

265
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:27,870
where we will increment
the underlying key material

266
00:12:27,870 --> 00:12:31,320
and just a lot of genuine
value that comes from the fact

267
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:33,003
that you're integrating with KMS.

268
00:12:34,890 --> 00:12:38,410
So there are a couple of
different kinds of KMS

269
00:12:39,270 --> 00:12:42,540
that all has a top layer, the KMS APIs.

270
00:12:42,540 --> 00:12:44,010
Then there's a second layer,

271
00:12:44,010 --> 00:12:45,963
which is where the keys actually live.

272
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:52,230
The best solution for
effectively all customers

273
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:57,060
is regular KMS where the key
material is both generated

274
00:12:57,060 --> 00:13:00,810
within and used for
cryptographic operations

275
00:13:00,810 --> 00:13:03,870
within KMS multi-tenant HSMs.

276
00:13:03,870 --> 00:13:06,360
And again, these things are the real deal.

277
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:09,630
They are bespoke, they're
built to our design

278
00:13:09,630 --> 00:13:11,490
and they are FIPS validated.

279
00:13:11,490 --> 00:13:15,330
And point in fact, the
entire box is FIPS validated.

